Package rocks.xmpp.extensions.pubsub.model

Class PublishOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • rocks.xmpp.extensions.pubsub.model.PublishOptions
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StandardizedDataForm
    public final class PublishOptions
extends Object
implements StandardizedDataForm
    Represents a standardized DataForm with form type http://jabber.org/protocol/pubsub#publish-options, which can be used to retrieve node meta data.

    Usage

    To wrap an existing DataForm to retrieve standard data from it, use: 
    
 PublishOptions publishOptions = new PublishOptions(dataForm);
    To build a form: 
    
 PublishOptions publishOptions = PublishOptions.builder()
     .accessModel(AccessModel.AUTHORIZE)
     .persistItems(true)
     .rosterGroupsAllowed(Collections.singleton("Friends"))
     .sendLastPublishedItem(SendLastPublishedItem.ON_SUB)
     .build();

    Persistent Storage of Public Data via PubSub

    
 PublishOptions publishOptions = PublishOptions.forStorageOfPublicData();

    Persistent Storage of Public Private via PubSub

    
 PublishOptions publishOptions = PublishOptions.forStorageOfPrivateData();
    See Also:
    16.4.5 pubsub#publish-options FORM_TYPE, 7.1.5 Publishing Options, XEP-0222: Persistent Storage of Public Data via PubSub, XEP-0223: Persistent Storage of Private Data via PubSub
